# Inventory Management System (IMS) — System Report

**Project:** Scalable Web-Based Inventory Management System  
**Date:** 2026-03-08  
**Version:** 1.0.0  

---

## 1. Executive Summary

The Inventory Management System (IMS) is a **multi-tenant, role-based web application** designed for managing products, stock levels, orders, branches, and users. It follows a **three-tier architecture**:

| Layer | Technology | Status |
|-------|-----------|--------|
| **Frontend** | React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 7 + Tailwind CSS 4 | ✅ Implemented |
| **Backend** | Python FastAPI + Pydantic v2 | ✅ Implemented |
| **Database** | Supabase (PostgreSQL 17) with RLS | ✅ Deployed |
| **Realtime** | Supabase Realtime (WebSocket) | ✅ Configured |

The system is hosted on **Supabase** (`eu-central-1` region) and uses **Supabase Auth** for JWT-based authentication. The database schema consists of **10 tables**, **32 RLS policies**, **23 indexes**, and a critical **RPC function** for atomic stock management.

---

## 2. System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Frontend — React + Vite + TypeScript"
        A[React SPA] --> B[TanStack Query v5]
        A --> C[React Router v7]
        A --> D[Tailwind CSS Components]
    end

    subgraph "Backend — FastAPI"
        E[FastAPI Server] --> F[JWT Auth Middleware]
        E --> G[Business Logic Services]
        E --> H[RBAC Permissions Layer]
    end

    subgraph "Supabase Platform"
        I[(PostgreSQL 17 + RLS)]
        J[Supabase Auth]
        K[Supabase Realtime]
    end

    B -->|REST API| E
    A -->|Realtime WS| K
    F -->|Verify JWT| J
    G -->|Supabase Client| I
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All data mutations flow through the **FastAPI backend**, which enforces RBAC and delegates stock changes to the database's `adjust_stock_level()` RPC for atomic, race-condition-safe updates.

