## 5. Backend Implementation

### 5.1 Application Entry Point

The FastAPI app is defined in [main.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/main.py) with:
- CORS middleware (currently allows all origins)
- Health check endpoint (`/api/v1/health`)
- 6 registered API routers

### 5.2 API Routers (6 total)

| Router | Prefix | File | Endpoints |
|--------|--------|------|-----------|
| Dashboard | `/api/v1/dashboard` | [dashboard.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/dashboard.py) | `GET /summary` |
| Products | `/api/v1/products` | [products.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/products.py) | `GET /`, `GET /{id}`, `POST /`, `PUT /{id}`, `DELETE /{id}` |
| Stock | `/api/v1/stock` | [stock.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/stock.py) | `GET /`, `POST /adjust`, `POST /transfer` |
| Orders | `/api/v1/orders` | [orders.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/orders.py) | CRUD + status management |
| Branches | `/api/v1/branches` | [branches.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/branches.py) | CRUD |
| Users | `/api/v1/users` | [users.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/routers/users.py) | User management |

### 5.3 Service Layer (3 services)

| Service | File | Responsibility |
|---------|------|---------------|
| ProductService | [product_service.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/services/product_service.py) | Product CRUD operations |
| StockService | [stock_service.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/services/stock_service.py) | Stock adjustment via RPC, inter-branch transfers |
| OrderService | [order_service.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/services/order_service.py) | Order creation and status management |

### 5.4 Authentication & Authorization

| Component | File | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| JWT Middleware | [middleware.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/middleware.py) | Validates JWT via Supabase Auth, fetches user profile with role/branch |
| RBAC Permissions | [permissions.py](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/permissions.py) | [require_role()](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/permissions.py#5-17), [require_admin()](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/permissions.py#18-20), [require_manager()](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/permissions.py#21-23), [require_staff()](file:///w:/level%203/Software/System/backend/app/auth/permissions.py#24-26) |

**Authentication Flow:**
1. Client sends JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
2. Middleware calls `supabase.auth.get_user(token)` to verify validity
3. Fetches user profile from `profiles` table for role and branch assignment
4. Returns user context `{id, email, role, branch_id, jwt}` to route handlers

